OL,3,CCommunities with high flood risk 'face
OL,4,Cservice cuts' as defence costs rise
OL,6,FInternal drainage boards have seen
OL,7,Ftheir costs increase by an average of
OL,8,F28% since 2022-23, largely as a result
OL,9,Fof higher energy and fuel prices,
OL,10,Fincreasingly extreme wet weather
OL,11,Fevents and wage increases, according
OL,12,Fto the District Councils' Network
OL,13,F(DCN).
OL,15,FCurrently district councils, or
OL,16,Funitary councils in some areas,
OL,17,Fcollect levies on behalf of the
OL,18,Fboards, which are small public bodies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
