OL,3,CCommunities with high flood risk 'face
OL,4,Cservice cuts' as defence costs rise
OL,6,FFor example, the Middle Level
OL,7,FCommissioners, which manage water
OL,8,Flevels in the Fens, is said to be
OL,9,Ffacing a 509% increase in its standing
OL,10,Fcharges.
OL,12,FThe DCN said potential solutions could
OL,13,Finclude the Government funding the
OL,14,Ffull costs of drainage boards to
OL,15,Fcouncils as a relatively small
OL,16,Fproportion of authorities are affected.
OL,18,FOther suggestions include the removal
OL,19,Fof the council tax cap to generate for
OL,20,Ffunding or new legislation to remove
OL,21,Flevies from council tax bills.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
