OL,3,CCommunities with high flood risk 'face
OL,4,Cservice cuts' as defence costs rise
OL,6,FHe added: "The embedded cost is one
OL,7,Fthat our councils simply can no longer
OL,8,Fafford. Its impact is becoming more
OL,9,Fsignificant every year that passes and
OL,10,Fit is not going to go away. We need
OL,11,Fthe Government to listen and work with
OL,12,Fus to deliver a long-term solution at
OL,13,Fpace.
OL,15,F"Councils are already in a precarious
OL,16,Fposition on the services they can
OL,17,Fafford to provide and have difficult
OL,18,Fdecisions to come."
OL,20,FThe Government has been approached for
OL,21,Fcomment.
